{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_33","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `com.h2database:h2:2.2.220`, but the preserved work looks actionable: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-730-fails-java-run-com.h2database-h2-2.2.220-6bd4fc9e\n\nMost likely failing stage: `native-test-verify`, and the failure looks like an interrupted job rather than a remaining H2 runtime regression. `human-intervention-logs/com.h2database:h2:2.2.220/native-test-verify/cycle-0-test-2026-05-05T04-53-10-298114Z.log` ends with `Gradle build daemon has been stopped: stop command received`. In contrast, `human-intervention-logs/com.h2database:h2:2.2.220/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-05T05-06-27-192648Z.log` shows the generated H2 suite passing (`22 successful`, `2 aborted`, `0 failed`) and `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`, and `human-intervention-logs/com.h2database:h2:2.2.220/checkstyle/pi-checkstyle-2026-05-05T05-08-30-921710Z.log` also ends `BUILD SUCCESSFUL`.\n\nThere is also evidence that the generated metadata initially needed cleanup rather than a new test fix. `human-intervention-logs/com.h2database:h2:2.2.220/metadata-fix/codex.log` says the real defect was exposed by `checkMetadataFiles`: the generated `metadata/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/reachability-metadata.json` contained invalid `condition.typeReached` entries pointing at `h2.*` test classes instead of `org.h2.*` runtime types. After correcting that, both `checkMetadataFiles` and `test` passed on the preserved branch. Metrics were recorded successfully in `stats/com.h2database/h2/2.2.220/execution-metrics.json`, and dynamic-access coverage improved from `11/101` on `2.1.210` to `58/102` on `2.2.220`.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.h2database:h2:2.2.220/native-test-verify/cycle-0-test-2026-05-05T04-53-10-298114Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/com.h2database:h2:2.2.220/gradle-test/gradle-test-20